    <title>EmptyLineWrappingInBlock</title>
  </head>
  <body>
    <section name="EmptyLineWrappingInBlock">
      <p>Since Checkstyle 13.4.0</p>
      <subsection name="Description" id="EmptyLineWrappingInBlock_Description">
        <div>
          Checks the presence or absence of empty lines at the top and bottom of code blocks
          (e.g. class, method, if, for). Configurable per block kind via <code>tokens</code>.
        </div>

        <p>
          For each configured block type, <code>topSeparator</code> controls the empty line
          at the start of the block (before the first statement);
          <code>bottomSeparator</code> controls the empty line at the end (after the last statement).
        </p>

        <p>
          Policy values: <code>empty_line</code> (exactly one required), <code>empty_line_allowed</code>
          (no validation), <code>no_empty_line</code> (forbidden).
        </p>

        <p>
          See <a href="https://github.com/checkstyle/checkstyle/issues/5313">#5313</a>.
        </p>
      </subsection>

